<subSubSection id="28C6AE65E3FF3E7B385B1FC810873B2B" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="A3A7AA0F88F3D0852618A666D258E3EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Habitat and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D88288BDB3C59B10D469ED14ADAE2BC2" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Scattered on soil in tropical forests dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="BB4AD85AFD116D4B711BCE760663DFCF" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Castanopsis" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="285F30626F377EB8A408C837E269BCEB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Castanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="DC8F2EBAF408C519C6951EAD615AC154" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="E22C6776FF82E8DF6E485C51BCC2F787" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2567283972F6EF618067C1F602B70FAA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="7736C7A55DF91BA4343CBE50146D10ED" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="F5885E321D4EB3BCA88D5F2B1B78A894" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pinus" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Coniferophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="826537359AB02485F5980BF58B49D51B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="E55DBFD68F2A673028B1BAC4381FFAEF" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Coniferophyta" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
). Currently known from southern and south-western China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="838A9FD6FF21718AE8507816D7EC8978" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2A360A1DFA045DEF0AC17436CFDA204D" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="89157153CF8C839A416CC102FED62D18" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
<taxonomicName id="EC6DEF4F33898F85F6238FF59B384E8E" authorityName="T. H. Li, W. Q. Deng &amp; B. Song, Fungal Diversity 12: 123" authorityYear="2013" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="Gyroporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gyroporus brunneofloccosus" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brunneofloccosus">
<emphasis id="93F1491BC13B516EB4AA714C9DB79B36" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Gyroporus brunneofloccosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally described from southern China, is characterised by the initially dark brown to brown and then brown to light red-brown pileus with concolorous floccose-scaly to coarsely tomentose squamules, the extended pileal margin, the white pileal context staining cerulean blue or greenish-blue to dark blue or deep blue when bruised, the initially yellowish to pale yellow and then greenish-yellow hymenophore staining cerulean blue to greenish-blue when bruised, the brownish to brown or light red-brown stipe, the spongy and then hollow context in the stipe, the frequent clamp connections in all tissues, the ellipsoid basidiospores and the distribution in tropical forests dominated by plants of the families 
<taxonomicName id="07D338EE9E614949AAFFE5455844BC92" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Fagaceae" genus="Gyroporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F20A574C1656E64F237CFF218DC9B613" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pinaceae" genus="Gyroporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9980134EB37A28D77EC06077EEA0D513" author="Li, TH" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="123 - 127" publicationUrl="https://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/FD12-123-127.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Li, TH, Deng, WQ, Song, B, 2003. A new cyanescent species of Gyroporus from China. Fungal Diversity 12: 123 - 127, https://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/FD12-123-127.pdf" title="A new cyanescent species of Gyroporus from China." url="https://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/FD12-123-127.pdf" volume="12" year="2003">Li et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D115CE88D4DB61D44D3E65FBFA3C2753" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
In China, 
<taxonomicName id="F7A8C2A6D21367F4B5834A50AFEF57A0" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. brunneofloccosus" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brunneofloccosus">
<emphasis id="3968F293E2EC7C4C0A268ECAEE6B5086" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">G. brunneofloccosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="A12E851802D2BF95A1B7CE3A884E8C0A" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. cyanescens" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cyanescens">
<emphasis id="A7AD38CC3BC18BEA4E793FA73F1FA09C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">G. cyanescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Bi et al. (1990, 
<bibRefCitation id="4CEE4A7CDE75AFB1A44D53B8761D6F6F" author="Bi, ZS" journalOrPublisher="Guangdong Science and Technology, Guangdong" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" publicationUrl="https://book.ixueshu.com/book/bf3d5f8d7bd973ed.html" refId="B3" refString="Bi, ZS, Zheng, GY, Li, TH, 1994. Macrofungus Flora of Guangdong Province. Guangdong Science and Technology, Guangdong, https://book.ixueshu.com/book/bf3d5f8d7bd973ed.html" title="Macrofungus Flora of Guangdong Province." url="https://book.ixueshu.com/book/bf3d5f8d7bd973ed.html" year="1994">1994</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="026DC0956F4D343C6CDEF921134C1B95" author="Ying, JZ" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" publicationUrl="https://book.ixueshu.com/book/a3f03cd59a016ac3.html" refId="B37" refString="Ying, JZ, Zang, M, 1994. Economic Macrofungi from South-western China. Science Press, Beijing, https://book.ixueshu.com/book/a3f03cd59a016ac3.html" title="Economic Macrofungi from South-western China." url="https://book.ixueshu.com/book/a3f03cd59a016ac3.html" year="1994">Ying and Zang (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="3B0951733F2351E562FFC75CF0A0B4E1" author="Mao, XL" journalOrPublisher="Henan Science and Technology Press, Zhengzhou" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" publicationUrl="https://book.douban.com/subject/1433850/" refId="B25" refString="Mao, XL, 2000. The Macrofungi in China. Henan Science and Technology Press, Zhengzhou, https://book.douban.com/subject/1433850/" title="The Macrofungi in China." url="https://book.douban.com/subject/1433850/" year="2000">Mao (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. However, these two species can be separated both by phylogenetic and morphological evidence. Our phylogenetic analysis of 
<emphasis id="92EE9D53C521AEEAAFDC3D6F9865C7EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">atp6</emphasis>
data (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1FACD492CE2CB89AF72537FB85C391D9" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Maximum Likelihood phylogenetic tree of Gyroporus inferred from the atp 6 dataset. Bootstrap frequencies (&gt; 50 %) are shown above or below supported branches. Newly-sequenced collections are indicated in bold. Species vouchers and countries of origin are provided after the species name successively." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.81.65660.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/570653" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">1</figureCitation>
) indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="614CA16F8FDB2DA7F20877108A5A48AB" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. brunneofloccosus" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brunneofloccosus">
<emphasis id="3E236E8A8523255451166F618A5F94E4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">G. brunneofloccosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="5B53685AEE2A599C90BC6361A4CB0148" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. phaeocyanescens" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="phaeocyanescens">
<emphasis id="37E6F648A1549697089BEB393E47EBDF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">G. phaeocyanescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="FD12874C699A4BF0EF847511C0FCEB11" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. phaeocyanescens" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="phaeocyanescens">
<emphasis id="B27AF55C072C8DB537BCF83DD298CF7E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">G. phaeocyanescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally described from Belize by 
<bibRefCitation id="A32C98DE942DE8F15BD64FCB0641087E" author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte zur Nova Hedwigia" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="1 - 352" publicationUrl="https://www.cabdirect.org/cabdirect/abstract/19841394943" refId="B30" refString="Singer, R, Araujo, I, Ivory, MH, 1983. The ectotrophically mycorrhizal fungi of the neotropical lowlands, especially central Amazonia. Beihefte zur Nova Hedwigia 77: 1 - 352, https://www.cabdirect.org/cabdirect/abstract/19841394943" title="The ectotrophically mycorrhizal fungi of the neotropical lowlands, especially central Amazonia." url="https://www.cabdirect.org/cabdirect/abstract/19841394943" volume="77" year="1983">Singer et al. (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, has fulvous to snuff brown pileus and relatively large basidiospores measuring 9.3-14.7 
<normalizedToken id="9DF94CE1411BD351A0E409FEDC125D63" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5.3-6.7 
<normalizedToken id="5CA7D59A63DC5A7F48585A0C852074D4" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7524EAE1516C0AF3935EB1EFE682FC47" author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte zur Nova Hedwigia" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="1 - 352" publicationUrl="https://www.cabdirect.org/cabdirect/abstract/19841394943" refId="B30" refString="Singer, R, Araujo, I, Ivory, MH, 1983. The ectotrophically mycorrhizal fungi of the neotropical lowlands, especially central Amazonia. Beihefte zur Nova Hedwigia 77: 1 - 352, https://www.cabdirect.org/cabdirect/abstract/19841394943" title="The ectotrophically mycorrhizal fungi of the neotropical lowlands, especially central Amazonia." url="https://www.cabdirect.org/cabdirect/abstract/19841394943" volume="77" year="1983">Singer et al. 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D8D2DC21537A52F6CFA966D926364577" author="Li, TH" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="123 - 127" publicationUrl="https://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/FD12-123-127.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Li, TH, Deng, WQ, Song, B, 2003. A new cyanescent species of Gyroporus from China. Fungal Diversity 12: 123 - 127, https://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/FD12-123-127.pdf" title="A new cyanescent species of Gyroporus from China." url="https://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/FD12-123-127.pdf" volume="12" year="2003">Li et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
